If you are using the Apache SDK in your Android app, and you want to stop it from collecting the Android ID before obtaining user consent, you can follow these steps:

1. Update the Apache SDK to the latest version: Make sure that you are using the latest version of the Apache SDK in your app. This may include updating the Apache SDK library in your app's build.gradle file.
2. Disable Android ID collection: In the Apache SDK initialization code, disable the collection of the Android ID by passing `false` as the value for the `enableAndroidId` parameter. This will prevent the Apache SDK from collecting the Android ID before obtaining user consent. Here's an example:
```java
import com.adobe.marketing.mobile.*;

// ...

public class MyApplication extends Application {
    @Override
    public void onCreate() {
        super.onCreate();

        // Initialize the Apache SDK
        Config.setContext(this);
        MobileCore.setApplication(this);
        MobileCore.setLogLevel(LoggingMode.DEBUG);

        // Disable Android ID collection
        MobileCore.setPrivacyStatus(MobilePrivacyStatus.OPT_IN);
        MobileCore.setAdvertisingIdentifierEnabled(false);

        // ...
    }
}
```
In this example, the `MobileCore.setAdvertisingIdentifierEnabled(false)` line disables the collection of the Android ID.

3. Obtain user consent: Implement a user consent flow in your app that allows the user to grant or deny consent for data collection. Once the user grants consent, you can enable the collection of the Android ID by passing `true` as the value for the `enableAndroidId` parameter in the Apache SDK initialization code.
```java
import com.adobe.marketing.mobile.*;

// ...

public class MyApplication extends Application {
    @Override
    public void onCreate() {
        super.onCreate();

        // Initialize the Apache SDK
        Config.setContext(this);
        MobileCore.setApplication(this);
        MobileCore.setLogLevel(LoggingMode.DEBUG);

        // Obtain user consent
        MobileCore.setPrivacyStatus(MobilePrivacyStatus.OPT_IN);

        // Enable Android ID collection
        MobileCore.setAdvertisingIdentifierEnabled(true);

        // ...
    }
}
```
In this example, the `MobileCore.setAdvertisingIdentifierEnabled(true)` line enables the collection of the Android ID.

By following these steps, you can prevent the Apache SDK from collecting the Android ID before obtaining user consent in your Android app.

